"{\"uid\": \"wired.com-story-nbc-peacock-2024-summer-olympics-coverage\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"I start everymorning of the Summer Games the same way: by turning on the living room TV, saying the word \\\"Olympics\\\" into a Comcast-powered remote control, and clicking the Gold Zone icon.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 187, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Summer Games\", \"from\": 24, \"to\": 40}, {\"ngram\": \"the living room TV\", \"from\": 69, \"to\": 87}, {\"ngram\": \"the word\", \"from\": 96, \"to\": 104}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"Olympics\", \"from\": 105, \"to\": 114}, {\"ngram\": \"a Comcast-powered remote control\", \"from\": 121, \"to\": 153}, {\"ngram\": \"the Gold Zone icon\", \"from\": 168, \"to\": 186}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's like putting my TV set on autopilot.\", \"from\": 188, \"to\": 229, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my TV\", \"from\": 206, \"to\": 211}, {\"ngram\": \"autopilot\", \"from\": 219, \"to\": 228}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the rest of the day Comcast's NBCUniversal is in charge, showing skateboarding or swimming one minute, fencing or field hockey the next-and sometimes 10 sports in 10 boxes simultaneously.\", \"from\": 230, \"to\": 421, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the rest\", \"from\": 234, \"to\": 242}, {\"ngram\": \"the day\", \"from\": 246, \"to\": 253}, {\"ngram\": \"Comcast's NBCUniversal\", \"from\": 254, \"to\": 276}, {\"ngram\": \"charge\", \"from\": 283, \"to\": 289}, {\"ngram\": \"sometimes 10 sports\", \"from\": 374, \"to\": 393}, {\"ngram\": \"10 boxes\", \"from\": 397, \"to\": 405}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I call my kids over to the TV when Team USA is about to win a medal.\", \"from\": 422, \"to\": 490, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 457, \"end\": 465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999822921383, \"rank\": 1.755236528791154e-08, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my kids\", \"from\": 429, \"to\": 436}, {\"ngram\": \"the TV\", \"from\": 445, \"to\": 451}, {\"ngram\": \"a medal\", \"from\": 482, \"to\": 489}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I mute it for long stretches of the day.\", \"from\": 491, \"to\": 531, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"long stretches\", \"from\": 505, \"to\": 519}, {\"ngram\": \"the day\", \"from\": 523, \"to\": 530}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's like having a live portal to Paris, or at least a very sophisticated screensaver.\", \"from\": 532, \"to\": 618, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 566, \"end\": 571, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.701208259522989e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a live portal\", \"from\": 549, \"to\": 562}, {\"ngram\": \"at least a very sophisticated screensaver\", \"from\": 576, \"to\": 617}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You may experience the Olympics in a totally different fashion.\", \"from\": 620, \"to\": 683, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 639, \"to\": 651}, {\"ngram\": \"a totally different fashion\", \"from\": 655, \"to\": 682}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Maybe you swipe through videoclips on TikTok.\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 729, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 722, \"end\": 728, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1586213250606448e-75, \"text\": \"TikTok\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"videoclips\", \"from\": 708, \"to\": 718}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Maybe you stream the raw feeds of your favorite obscure sport on Peacock.\", \"from\": 730, \"to\": 803, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 795, \"end\": 802, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4449772230974363e-19, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the raw feeds\", \"from\": 747, \"to\": 760}, {\"ngram\": \"your favorite obscure sport\", \"from\": 764, \"to\": 791}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Maybe you watch NBC's whiz-bang prime time recap.\", \"from\": 804, \"to\": 853, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 820, \"end\": 823, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9983495210264104, \"rank\": 0.00165042604546889, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Maybe you tune into some highlight show I have not even discovered yet.\", \"from\": 854, \"to\": 925, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some highlight show\", \"from\": 874, \"to\": 893}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ultimately, we are all still watching the same global spectacle, albeit from different angles and with different narrators.\", \"from\": 926, \"to\": 1049, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the same global spectacle\", \"from\": 964, \"to\": 989}, {\"ngram\": \"different angles\", \"from\": 1003, \"to\": 1019}, {\"ngram\": \"different narrators\", \"from\": 1029, \"to\": 1048}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a rare instance of fragmentation being to streaming's benefit; the Olympics illustrate how all the shattered pieces can be stuck back together.\", \"from\": 1051, \"to\": 1199, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a rare instance\", \"from\": 1056, \"to\": 1071}, {\"ngram\": \"fragmentation\", \"from\": 1075, \"to\": 1088}, {\"ngram\": \"streaming's benefit\", \"from\": 1098, \"to\": 1117}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1119, \"to\": 1131}, {\"ngram\": \"all the shattered pieces\", \"from\": 1147, \"to\": 1171}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"These days, it's not often that we can unite people and bring them together around something,\\\" says Molly Solomon, executive producer and president of NBC Olympics Production.\", \"from\": 1200, \"to\": 1376, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1301, \"end\": 1306, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Molly_Hayes\", \"score\": 0.9984421255228855, \"rank\": 0.0015598803357594253, \"text\": \"Molly\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Molly_Hayes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Molly_Hayes\"}, {\"begin\": 1352, \"end\": 1364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBC Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1246, \"to\": 1252}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 1284, \"to\": 1293}, {\"ngram\": \"executive producer\", \"from\": 1316, \"to\": 1334}, {\"ngram\": \"president\", \"from\": 1339, \"to\": 1348}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Olympics is doing it.\\\"\", \"from\": 1377, \"to\": 1404, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympics\", \"from\": 1378, \"to\": 1390}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Randy Plemel, the founder of a design consultancy in Queens, New York, felt this effect when his family wanted to watch the US Women's National Team soccer match and gymnastics superstar Simone Biles at the same time last week.\", \"from\": 1406, \"to\": 1633, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1467, \"end\": 1475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999999999199645, \"rank\": 7.357598172322201e-11, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}, {\"begin\": 1530, \"end\": 1532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.7087774909307747, \"rank\": 0.41075061524124007, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1593, \"end\": 1605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Randy Plemel\", \"from\": 1406, \"to\": 1418}, {\"ngram\": \"the founder\", \"from\": 1420, \"to\": 1431}, {\"ngram\": \"a design consultancy\", \"from\": 1435, \"to\": 1455}, {\"ngram\": \"Queens\", \"from\": 1459, \"to\": 1465}, {\"ngram\": \"this effect\", \"from\": 1482, \"to\": 1493}, {\"ngram\": \"his family\", \"from\": 1499, \"to\": 1509}, {\"ngram\": \"gymnastics superstar\", \"from\": 1572, \"to\": 1592}, {\"ngram\": \"the same time\", \"from\": 1609, \"to\": 1622}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His solution: Multiview, a Peacock feature that splits the big screen between multiple events, \\\"thus keeping a harmonious home,\\\" he says.\", \"from\": 1634, \"to\": 1771, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1648, \"end\": 1657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amiga_support_and_maintenance_software\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Multiview\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amiga_support_and_maintenance_software\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amiga_support_and_maintenance_software\"}, {\"begin\": 1661, \"end\": 1668, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4449772230974363e-19, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the big screen\", \"from\": 1689, \"to\": 1703}, {\"ngram\": \"multiple events\", \"from\": 1712, \"to\": 1727}, {\"ngram\": \"a harmonious home\", \"from\": 1743, \"to\": 1760}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That approach has also helped Plemel expose his children to obscure competitions they would never ordinarily see.\", \"from\": 1773, \"to\": 1886, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"That approach\", \"from\": 1773, \"to\": 1786}, {\"ngram\": \"Plemel\", \"from\": 1803, \"to\": 1809}, {\"ngram\": \"his children\", \"from\": 1817, \"to\": 1829}, {\"ngram\": \"obscure competitions\", \"from\": 1833, \"to\": 1853}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(My own kids are suddenly into Ping Pong and canoe slalom.)\", \"from\": 1887, \"to\": 1946, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1923, \"end\": 1927, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pong\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4257602386431903e-35, \"text\": \"Pong\", \"types\": [\"Q7889\", \"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pong\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pong\"}, {\"begin\": 1938, \"end\": 1944, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slalom_skiing\", \"score\": 0.9999998806724832, \"rank\": 1.1932793838657256e-07, \"text\": \"slalom\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slalom_skiing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slalom_skiing\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"My own kids\", \"from\": 1888, \"to\": 1899}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other viewers are observing the games through Snoop Dogg's eyes, since the rapper is there on assignment for NBC, or streaming the soccer watch parties hosted by Alex Cooper, or catching up via Kevin Hart and Kenan Thompson'sOlympic Highlightscomedy show on Peacock.\", \"from\": 1947, \"to\": 2213, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1993, \"end\": 2003, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Snoop Dogg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\"}, {\"begin\": 2056, \"end\": 2059, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9983495210264104, \"rank\": 0.00165042604546889, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}, {\"begin\": 2109, \"end\": 2120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Cooper_(footballer)\", \"score\": 0.860757357501504, \"rank\": 0.1617647058823005, \"text\": \"Alex Cooper\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Cooper_(footballer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Cooper_(footballer)\"}, {\"begin\": 2141, \"end\": 2151, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Hart\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1501650816245903e-66, \"text\": \"Kevin Hart\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Hart\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Hart\"}, {\"begin\": 2205, \"end\": 2212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4449772230974363e-19, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Other viewers\", \"from\": 1947, \"to\": 1960}, {\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 1975, \"to\": 1984}, {\"ngram\": \"the rapper\", \"from\": 2018, \"to\": 2028}, {\"ngram\": \"assignment\", \"from\": 2041, \"to\": 2051}, {\"ngram\": \"the soccer watch parties\", \"from\": 2074, \"to\": 2098}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When Solomon mentioned the comic relief to me, I had to Google it; I did not even know it existed.\", \"from\": 2214, \"to\": 2312, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Solomon\", \"from\": 2219, \"to\": 2226}, {\"ngram\": \"the comic relief\", \"from\": 2237, \"to\": 2253}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But in a way, that's the point.\", \"from\": 2313, \"to\": 2344, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a way\", \"from\": 2320, \"to\": 2325}, {\"ngram\": \"the point\", \"from\": 2334, \"to\": 2343}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We think we have an answer for every type of viewing a consumer wants,\\\" Peacock president Kelly Campbell told me.\", \"from\": 2345, \"to\": 2459, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2436, \"end\": 2450, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Campbell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kelly Campbell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Campbell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Campbell\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an answer\", \"from\": 2363, \"to\": 2372}, {\"ngram\": \"every type\", \"from\": 2377, \"to\": 2387}, {\"ngram\": \"a consumer wants\", \"from\": 2399, \"to\": 2415}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some of the viewing types were science fiction back in 2014 when NBCUniversal, the media company owned by Comcast, agreed to pay $7.75 billion for the American rights to all Olympics telecasts between Beijing in 2022 and Brisbane in 2032.\", \"from\": 2461, \"to\": 2699, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2526, \"end\": 2538, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 6.35464448227528e-13, \"text\": \"NBCUniversal\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}, {\"begin\": 2567, \"end\": 2574, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Comcast\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1634790094744862e-14, \"text\": \"Comcast\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Comcast\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Comcast\"}, {\"begin\": 2612, \"end\": 2620, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television_in_the_United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3749787753750887e-14, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television_in_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television_in_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2662, \"end\": 2669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beijing\", \"score\": 0.7984972237284033, \"rank\": 0.21222669046187176, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beijing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beijing\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the viewing types\", \"from\": 2469, \"to\": 2486}, {\"ngram\": \"science fiction\", \"from\": 2492, \"to\": 2507}, {\"ngram\": \"the media company\", \"from\": 2540, \"to\": 2557}, {\"ngram\": \"all Olympics telecasts\", \"from\": 2631, \"to\": 2653}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Comcast chair Brian Roberts pointed out on CNBC last week that Olympics TV deals \\\"let you have all technologies,\\\" meaning NBC can distribute Olympics content in ways that did not exist a decade ago.\", \"from\": 2700, \"to\": 2898, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2700, \"end\": 2707, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Comcast\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1634790094744862e-14, \"text\": \"Comcast\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Comcast\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Comcast\"}, {\"begin\": 2714, \"end\": 2727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_L._Roberts\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.446530787955523e-30, \"text\": \"Brian Roberts\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_L._Roberts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brian_L._Roberts\"}, {\"begin\": 2743, \"end\": 2747, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5331792412825847e-28, \"text\": \"CNBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\"}, {\"begin\": 2772, \"end\": 2774, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television\", \"score\": 0.9999999999881766, \"rank\": 8.243555203817215e-12, \"text\": \"TV\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television\"}, {\"begin\": 2822, \"end\": 2825, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9983495210264104, \"rank\": 0.00165042604546889, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all technologies\", \"from\": 2795, \"to\": 2811}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympics content\", \"from\": 2841, \"to\": 2857}, {\"ngram\": \"ways\", \"from\": 2861, \"to\": 2865}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's how you get Peacock's daily recap videos narrated by anAI-generated version of legendary broadcaster Al Michaels, as well as dozens of daily @NBCOlympics clips on TikTok, a platform that wasn't invented until 2016.\", \"from\": 2899, \"to\": 3120, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2918, \"end\": 2925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4449772230974363e-19, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}, {\"begin\": 3007, \"end\": 3018, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Michaels\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4838275563258102e-51, \"text\": \"Al Michaels\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Michaels\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Michaels\"}, {\"begin\": 3069, \"end\": 3075, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1586213250606448e-75, \"text\": \"TikTok\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"anAI-generated version\", \"from\": 2959, \"to\": 2981}, {\"ngram\": \"dozens\", \"from\": 3031, \"to\": 3037}, {\"ngram\": \"daily @NBCOlympics clips\", \"from\": 3041, \"to\": 3065}, {\"ngram\": \"a platform\", \"from\": 3077, \"to\": 3087}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The highlight reels are yet another entry point into Olympics programming.\", \"from\": 3121, \"to\": 3195, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The highlight reels\", \"from\": 3121, \"to\": 3140}, {\"ngram\": \"another entry point\", \"from\": 3149, \"to\": 3168}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympics programming\", \"from\": 3174, \"to\": 3194}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NBC's have-it-your-way approach was borne out of technological necessity.\", \"from\": 3197, \"to\": 3270, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"your-way\", \"from\": 3211, \"to\": 3219}, {\"ngram\": \"technological necessity\", \"from\": 3246, \"to\": 3269}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Millions of viewers still like to wake up to theTodayshow's teary-eyed interviews with gold medalists and fall asleep to the prime time team's heartfelt come-from-behind stories.\", \"from\": 3271, \"to\": 3449, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Millions\", \"from\": 3271, \"to\": 3279}, {\"ngram\": \"viewers\", \"from\": 3283, \"to\": 3290}, {\"ngram\": \"theTodayshow's teary-eyed interviews\", \"from\": 3316, \"to\": 3352}, {\"ngram\": \"gold medalists\", \"from\": 3358, \"to\": 3372}, {\"ngram\": \"the prime time team's heartfelt come-from-behind stories\", \"from\": 3392, \"to\": 3448}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But that traditional production-gauzy, promotional, and packed with commercials-does not appeal to everyone, particularly in an age of instantaneous push alerts and social media memes about the games.\", \"from\": 3450, \"to\": 3650, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that traditional production-gauzy\", \"from\": 3454, \"to\": 3487}, {\"ngram\": \"commercials\", \"from\": 3518, \"to\": 3529}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 3549, \"to\": 3557}, {\"ngram\": \"an age\", \"from\": 3575, \"to\": 3581}, {\"ngram\": \"instantaneous push alerts\", \"from\": 3585, \"to\": 3610}, {\"ngram\": \"social media memes\", \"from\": 3615, \"to\": 3633}, {\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 3640, \"to\": 3649}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So for the first time, NBCUniversal decided to stop gatekeeping the hottest events of the day until US prime time.\", \"from\": 3651, \"to\": 3765, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3674, \"end\": 3686, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 6.35464448227528e-13, \"text\": \"NBCUniversal\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}, {\"begin\": 3751, \"end\": 3753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.7087774909307747, \"rank\": 0.41075061524124007, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 3658, \"to\": 3672}, {\"ngram\": \"the hottest events\", \"from\": 3715, \"to\": 3733}, {\"ngram\": \"the day\", \"from\": 3737, \"to\": 3744}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles' gold medal feats have been shown live during the day and again at night.\", \"from\": 3766, \"to\": 3845, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Biles' gold medal feats\", \"from\": 3766, \"to\": 3789}, {\"ngram\": \"the day\", \"from\": 3818, \"to\": 3825}, {\"ngram\": \"night\", \"from\": 3839, \"to\": 3844}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"No holding back\\\" is how Solomon describes it.\", \"from\": 3846, \"to\": 3892, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"No holding\", \"from\": 3847, \"to\": 3857}, {\"ngram\": \"Solomon\", \"from\": 3871, \"to\": 3878}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are here for the audience.\\\"\", \"from\": 3893, \"to\": 3924, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the audience\", \"from\": 3910, \"to\": 3922}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This has already redounded to NBC's and the International Olympic Committee's benefit.\", \"from\": 3926, \"to\": 4012, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3956, \"end\": 3959, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9983495210264104, \"rank\": 0.00165042604546889, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}, {\"begin\": 3970, \"end\": 4001, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Summer Olympics fever is real: NBC's TV ratings and streaming stats are both through the roof.\", \"from\": 4013, \"to\": 4107, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4044, \"end\": 4047, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9983495210264104, \"rank\": 0.00165042604546889, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Summer Olympics fever\", \"from\": 4013, \"to\": 4034}, {\"ngram\": \"streaming stats\", \"from\": 4065, \"to\": 4080}, {\"ngram\": \"the roof\", \"from\": 4098, \"to\": 4106}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Eight of Peacock's 10 most-streamed days of all time have been from these Olympics.\", \"from\": 4108, \"to\": 4191, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4117, \"end\": 4124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4449772230974363e-19, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all time\", \"from\": 4152, \"to\": 4160}, {\"ngram\": \"these Olympics\", \"from\": 4176, \"to\": 4190}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's been a complete turnaround for the streaming service, which disappointed users with a meager selection of streams during the Covid-delayed Tokyo games in 2021.\", \"from\": 4192, \"to\": 4356, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4336, \"end\": 4341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.99981093013305, \"rank\": 0.00018909652676978088, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a complete turnaround\", \"from\": 4202, \"to\": 4223}, {\"ngram\": \"the streaming service\", \"from\": 4228, \"to\": 4249}, {\"ngram\": \"users\", \"from\": 4270, \"to\": 4275}, {\"ngram\": \"a meager selection\", \"from\": 4281, \"to\": 4299}, {\"ngram\": \"streams\", \"from\": 4303, \"to\": 4310}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This time around, it just works.\", \"from\": 4358, \"to\": 4390, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Livestreams load quickly.\", \"from\": 4391, \"to\": 4416, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Livestreams\", \"from\": 4391, \"to\": 4402}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On-demand clips seamlessly play, one after another.\", \"from\": 4417, \"to\": 4468, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"-demand\", \"from\": 4419, \"to\": 4426}, {\"ngram\": \"another\", \"from\": 4460, \"to\": 4467}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NBC has managed to avoid what every streaming distributor dreads: Headlines about server meltdowns and software glitches.\", \"from\": 4469, \"to\": 4590, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4469, \"end\": 4472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9983495210264104, \"rank\": 0.00165042604546889, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"every streaming distributor\", \"from\": 4499, \"to\": 4526}, {\"ngram\": \"Headlines\", \"from\": 4535, \"to\": 4544}, {\"ngram\": \"server meltdowns\", \"from\": 4551, \"to\": 4567}, {\"ngram\": \"software glitches\", \"from\": 4572, \"to\": 4589}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We try to make livestreaming look easy, but actually it's not,\\\" Patrick Miceli, Peacock's chief technology officer, told me.\", \"from\": 4591, \"to\": 4716, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4656, \"end\": 4663, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Drake\", \"score\": 0.9546973052392571, \"rank\": 0.04745240231043516, \"text\": \"Patrick\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Drake\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Drake\"}, {\"begin\": 4672, \"end\": 4679, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4449772230974363e-19, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His team is handling up to 60 simultaneous live events, for a grand total of about 1,800 during the first week alone.\", \"from\": 4717, \"to\": 4834, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His team\", \"from\": 4717, \"to\": 4725}, {\"ngram\": \"up to 60 simultaneous live events\", \"from\": 4738, \"to\": 4771}, {\"ngram\": \"a grand total\", \"from\": 4777, \"to\": 4790}, {\"ngram\": \"the first week\", \"from\": 4813, \"to\": 4827}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This year is quite an inflection point,\\\" he says, \\\"in terms of what a streaming platform with live sports can do.\\\"\", \"from\": 4835, \"to\": 4950, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This year\", \"from\": 4836, \"to\": 4845}, {\"ngram\": \"quite an inflection point\", \"from\": 4849, \"to\": 4874}, {\"ngram\": \"terms\", \"from\": 4890, \"to\": 4895}, {\"ngram\": \"a streaming platform\", \"from\": 4904, \"to\": 4924}, {\"ngram\": \"live sports\", \"from\": 4930, \"to\": 4941}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Peacock's exclusive livestream of an NFL playoff game in January ranked as themost live-streamed gamein history, giving Miceli's team a boost of confidence that the service could hold up under the strain.\", \"from\": 4952, \"to\": 5156, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4952, \"end\": 4959, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4449772230974363e-19, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}, {\"begin\": 4989, \"end\": 4992, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NFL_on_CBS\", \"score\": 0.6234118750267647, \"rank\": 0.6040702691873759, \"text\": \"NFL\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NFL_on_CBS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NFL_on_CBS\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"January\", \"from\": 5009, \"to\": 5016}, {\"ngram\": \"themost live-streamed gamein history\", \"from\": 5027, \"to\": 5063}, {\"ngram\": \"Miceli's team\", \"from\": 5072, \"to\": 5085}, {\"ngram\": \"a boost\", \"from\": 5086, \"to\": 5093}, {\"ngram\": \"confidence\", \"from\": 5097, \"to\": 5107}, {\"ngram\": \"the service\", \"from\": 5113, \"to\": 5124}, {\"ngram\": \"the strain\", \"from\": 5145, \"to\": 5155}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the Summer Games are a unique beast.\", \"from\": 5157, \"to\": 5197, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Summer Games\", \"from\": 5161, \"to\": 5177}, {\"ngram\": \"a unique beast\", \"from\": 5182, \"to\": 5196}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hundreds of thousands of worker hours went into the engineering, product design, and marketing of the Olympics experience on Peacock, Campbell says.\", \"from\": 5198, \"to\": 5346, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5323, \"end\": 5330, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4449772230974363e-19, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}, {\"begin\": 5332, \"end\": 5340, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Campbell\", \"score\": 0.9999999999936335, \"rank\": 6.162437124995354e-12, \"text\": \"Campbell\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Campbell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Campbell\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Hundreds of thousands\", \"from\": 5198, \"to\": 5219}, {\"ngram\": \"worker hours\", \"from\": 5223, \"to\": 5235}, {\"ngram\": \"the engineering\", \"from\": 5246, \"to\": 5261}, {\"ngram\": \"product design\", \"from\": 5263, \"to\": 5277}, {\"ngram\": \"marketing\", \"from\": 5283, \"to\": 5292}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics experience\", \"from\": 5296, \"to\": 5319}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"For the first time, I really feel like we have solved the conundrum of navigation,\\\" she says.\", \"from\": 5348, \"to\": 5442, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 5353, \"to\": 5367}, {\"ngram\": \"the conundrum\", \"from\": 5403, \"to\": 5416}, {\"ngram\": \"navigation\", \"from\": 5420, \"to\": 5430}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The audience is always like, 'I am overwhelmed by the Summer Olympics.\", \"from\": 5443, \"to\": 5514, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The audience\", \"from\": 5444, \"to\": 5456}, {\"ngram\": \"the Summer Olympics\", \"from\": 5494, \"to\": 5513}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I can not find what I am looking for.'\", \"from\": 5515, \"to\": 5553, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I do think the interface and the dashboard of Peacock has really solved that.\\\"\", \"from\": 5554, \"to\": 5632, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5600, \"end\": 5607, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4449772230974363e-19, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the interface\", \"from\": 5565, \"to\": 5578}, {\"ngram\": \"the dashboard\", \"from\": 5583, \"to\": 5596}]}, {\"sentence\": \"DJ Jenkins, a pastor in Los Angeles, agrees.\", \"from\": 5634, \"to\": 5678, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5634, \"end\": 5636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.146235331393531e-20, \"text\": \"DJ\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\"}, {\"begin\": 5658, \"end\": 5669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.616772112114596e-22, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a pastor\", \"from\": 5646, \"to\": 5654}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He credits the Multiview functionality and Gold Zone-NBC's addictive way of one-upping the popular NFL RedZone format-with keeping him engaged in the games.\", \"from\": 5679, \"to\": 5835, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5778, \"end\": 5789, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resourc